<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-03-16T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-03-16T22:00:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">102.1/3–1745: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-03-17T10:00:00+07:00">March 17,
                                1945—10 a.m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received 11:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>453. To Secretary of Treasury from Adler.</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>United States Army no-rate in dollars expenditures. Advances by
                            Chinese Government January 3 billion, February 4 billion, while actual
                            disbursements by Army disbursing officers were 2.6 billion in January
                            and 2.19 billion in February for engineering commission to be expended
                            for United States Army construction and operations but actual
                            expenditures not yet known.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Fonanu Engineering Commission expenditures for United States Army
                            between 5 and 6 billion. [Adler.]</item>
                    </list>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>